I'm going to be needing


488
00:29:53.730 --> 00:29:56.370
extra cottage cheese and sugar.

489
00:29:56.690 --> 00:29:58.730
I'll give you all the ingredients.

490
00:29:58.810 --> 00:30:00.490
Give me some munchies.
- Fine, go ahead, eat.


491
00:30:01.850 --> 00:30:02.970
Roly-poly.

492
00:30:14.290 --> 00:30:15.170
Greetings.

493
00:30:16.010 --> 00:30:17.850
Goodness..
- Greetings..


494
00:31:08.610 --> 00:31:10.850
Hey.. - Please, Mr. Mahesh,
let me think.


495
00:31:11.450 --> 00:31:12.610
I just can't get it right..

496
00:31:18.650 --> 00:31:20.530
Oh, come on!
If you keep talking..


497
00:31:22.450 --> 00:31:23.370
What's going on?

498
00:31:23.850 --> 00:31:26.010
I-I..
I-I'm..


499
00:31:26.450 --> 00:31:28.210
I-I'm.. - What are you?
- I-I'm..


500
00:31:28.250 --> 00:31:29.850
What? An idiot?
- No..


501
00:31:29.970 --> 00:31:32.330
I'm trying to make a new dessert.

502
00:31:32.370 --> 00:31:34.530
It's made only of cottage cheese.

503
00:31:34.650 --> 00:31:37.050
It's soft and squishy.. And juicy..
- Only cottage cheese?


504
00:31:37.250 --> 00:31:39.450
If I add dried whole milk to it,
it won't be soft and squishy.


505
00:31:39.530 --> 00:31:41.530
So, I thought I'll use..
- How did you know that?


506
00:31:41.610 --> 00:31:44.650
I know. That's why..
- You know?


507
00:31:44.930 --> 00:31:46.290
You know all that
but you don't know


508
00:31:46.370 --> 00:31:48.370
that the sweet won't absorb
the syrup if it isn't fried!


509
00:31:48.410 --> 00:31:50.250
If I fry it,
it won't be white anymore.


510
00:31:50.450 --> 00:31:52.210
That's why I thought..
- So, you know more than me?


511
00:31:52.930 --> 00:31:54.810
You know more than Bhim Nag?
- Sir..


512
00:31:54.930 --> 00:31:56.610
No..
- Bhim Nag fried his sweets!


513
00:31:56.730 --> 00:31:58.290
That's how he could make
a special sweet for Lady Canning!


514
00:31:58.610 --> 00:32:00.610
If he hadn't fried the dough,
the way you don't want to


515
00:32:00.690 --> 00:32:02.170
Lady Canning wouldn't have got that
special dessert named after her!


516
00:32:02.290 --> 00:32:04.530
I was just trying to do it
in a novel manner.. - New! Novel!


517
00:32:04.930 --> 00:32:06.490
You think you can conquer the
world of desserts at the age of 20!


518
00:32:06.570 --> 00:32:07.610
You dare become so ambitious!

519
00:32:08.330 --> 00:32:09.370
There's no such thing
as a new dessert!


520
00:32:09.490 --> 00:32:10.850
You need to do
what everyone else is doing!


521
00:32:10.970 --> 00:32:13.210
He wants to make dessert..
- But everyone in Bengal


522
00:32:13.290 --> 00:32:15.130
is doing something new,
something novel.


523
00:32:15.410 --> 00:32:16.610
And I can't experiment
with desserts..


524
00:32:20.530 --> 00:32:22.370
You dare ruin a batch of sweets
and argue with me!


525
00:32:24.970 --> 00:32:27.650
And if you keep at it,
I'll kick you out of the shop!


526
00:32:30.210 --> 00:32:31.130
Mahesh!

527
00:32:31.850 --> 00:32:33.450
The Duttas from Bowbazar
have ordered some special sweets


528
00:32:33.530 --> 00:32:34.450
on account of '
Jamai Shashti'.

529
00:32:35.570 --> 00:32:37.410
Make sure no one taints
my reputation that day.


530
00:33:05.890 --> 00:33:06.770
Oh, God..

531
00:33:14.650 --> 00:33:15.570
Who is it..

532
00:33:16.930 --> 00:33:18.090
The Ganges is a nice and wide river

533
00:33:18.290 --> 00:33:19.850
but you didn't find a-anywhere else
to throw your guavas?


534
00:33:21.050 --> 00:33:21.970
I didn't throw any guavas at you.

535
00:33:22.010 --> 00:33:23.290
I saw you. So, I thought
of grabbing your attention.


536
00:33:23.930 --> 00:33:26.570
Oh, God..
- Hey! Do you have no job?


537
00:33:27.370 --> 00:33:29.450
'It will be done..'

538
00:33:29.530 --> 00:33:31.690
A dumpling soaked in syrup!
Rubbish!


539
00:33:32.210 --> 00:33:33.570
I told you.. It will be done.
You can take my word for it.


540
00:33:34.090 --> 00:33:35.050
A dumpling soaked in syrup..

541
00:33:35.570 --> 00:33:38.330
I won't rest until it's done.
- Of course!


542
00:33:38.450 --> 00:33:40.690
He says he won't rest
until he makes it! - Oh, be quiet!


543
00:33:41.010 --> 00:33:43.890
Why? Why should I be quiet?
You're a lazy bum.


544
00:33:43.970 --> 00:33:46.650
People with a job, work.
They don't stare at the Ganges.


545
00:33:47.530 --> 00:33:50.770
Then what are you doing here?

546
00:33:51.290 --> 00:33:52.490
As if you have a ton of work..

547
00:33:52.650 --> 00:33:55.290
Go on.. Go find a tree
infested with spirits.


548
00:33:55.410 --> 00:33:57.330
I'll teach you a lesson..
- You troublemaker! You imp!


549
00:33:57.410 --> 00:33:58.490
Oh, God..
Hey!


550
00:33:59.290 --> 00:34:00.170
Rubbish..

551
00:34:03.010 --> 00:34:05.490
Oh, God..
Stop throwing guavas at me..


552
00:34:05.610 --> 00:34:09.210
Oh, God..
- Rubbish.. - Sorry.. Stop..


553
00:34:09.770 --> 00:34:10.650
Oh, God..

554
00:34:10.970 --> 00:34:12.730
Now, do you understand
how it feels? - Get lost!


555
00:34:13.250 --> 00:34:14.130
Rubbish..

556
00:34:15.130 --> 00:34:17.210
Thank God..
Oh, God..


557
00:34:17.730 --> 00:34:19.810
If you don't have sweet thoughts
and you don't utter sweet words


558
00:34:20.050 --> 00:34:21.610
how will you be good
at making sweets?


559
00:34:22.530 --> 00:34:24.930
Is this the way to talk to girls?

560
00:34:26.290 --> 00:34:29.210
If a confectioner's behaviour
and words aren't nice


561
00:34:29.970 --> 00:34:32.370
he can't make good sweets.
Do you understand?


562
00:34:35.530 --> 00:34:37.890
Look at him..
He's preaching to me about sweets.


563
00:34:39.290 --> 00:34:40.330
Oh, Lord..

564
00:34:42.330 --> 00:34:44.010
Hey!
Watch that tone of yours!


565
00:34:44.170 --> 00:34:46.610
Do you know who made that
special dessert for Lady Canning?


566
00:34:46.930 --> 00:34:50.050
He did!
- Bhim Nag! - Yes!


567
00:35:33.690 --> 00:35:36.290
Who have you brought
with you, Rupa?


568
00:35:36.890 --> 00:35:39.970
This confectioner is a child.
- Mahesh, the confectioner, said


569
00:35:40.210 --> 00:35:43.170
that he can make novel desserts
and sweets.


570
00:35:43.490 --> 00:35:44.770
Please give me a chance.

571
00:35:45.210 --> 00:35:47.410
I'll be able to do it, ma'am.
- Great.


572
00:35:48.690 --> 00:35:51.610
Rupa, you can leave.
- Okay.


573
00:35:51.730 --> 00:35:53.850
I need to have a word with him
in private. - Okay.


574
00:35:56.050 --> 00:35:57.970
I won't be able to turn my neck
every time I have to talk to you.


575
00:35:58.090 --> 00:36:00.530
You need to come stand
in front of me. - What.. Okay.


576
00:36:06.810 --> 00:36:08.330
I have three sons-in-law.

577
00:36:09.010 --> 00:36:10.770
You need to make
a special dessert for them.


578
00:36:11.450 --> 00:36:12.330
Will you be able to do it?

579
00:36:12.890 --> 00:36:15.890
Don't nod your head arrogantly!
Listen to me first!


580
00:36:16.090 --> 00:36:18.210
All three of my sons-in-law
are out of this world!


581
00:36:19.090 --> 00:36:20.850
The eldest one is an addict.

582
00:36:21.290 --> 00:36:23.730
He lies wasted with his friends
all day long. - For shame..


583
00:36:23.850 --> 00:36:26.490
Marijuana.. He doesn't even
listen to his father-in-law!


584
00:36:26.570 --> 00:36:28.330
Do you understand?
Today is 'Shashti'.


585
00:36:28.410 --> 00:36:30.170
So, I had to round up
all three of them today.


586
00:36:31.810 --> 00:36:33.290
And the middle one..

587
00:36:33.370 --> 00:36:36.290
He has almost turned British
because he rubs elbows with them.


588
00:36:36.410 --> 00:36:38.370
He doesn't like Indian cuisine
anymore.


589
00:36:38.450 --> 00:36:41.490
He only likes the food
prepared by British people.


590
00:36:41.650 --> 00:36:42.770
And the youngest one..

591
00:36:42.890 --> 00:36:45.770
He has his nose buried into
either books or newspapers.


592
00:36:45.890 --> 00:36:48.290
He reads a few books
and starts preaching to people.


593
00:36:49.530 --> 00:36:51.770
You have to enchant
all three of them.


594
00:36:52.730 --> 00:36:56.370
Will you be able to do it?
- Enchant them! M-Me?


595
00:36:57.370 --> 00:37:01.810
No, ma'am.. A-Actually,
I-I'm not a very educated man.


596
00:37:02.250 --> 00:37:04.010
My father died before I was born.

597
00:37:04.250 --> 00:37:06.170
And my mother alone..
- Goodness! Listen, boy.


598
00:37:06.330 --> 00:37:09.450
I didn't ask you to have
an intellectual battle with them.


599
00:37:09.570 --> 00:37:12.370
Oh..
- You need to enchant them


600
00:37:12.450 --> 00:37:13.890
by making a new dessert
and feeding it to them.


601
00:37:14.450 --> 00:37:17.690
The dessert you make should be such
that no matter what happens


602
00:37:17.770 --> 00:37:19.730
they shouldn't be able
to badmouth it.


603
00:37:19.770 --> 00:37:22.090
Will you be able to do it?
- Yes..


604
00:37:23.010 --> 00:37:26.330
It doesn't seem so.
- No.. I'll be able to do it..


605
00:37:26.650 --> 00:37:28.250
Let me make something very clear..

606
00:37:28.850 --> 00:37:32.450
I won't be able to give you
more than 1 anna per sweet


607
00:37:32.730 --> 00:37:34.850
no matter what Mr. Kali
said to you.


608
00:37:44.170 --> 00:37:47.290
Sugar..
Cottage cheese..


609
00:37:48.210 --> 00:37:49.370
Dried whole milk..

610
00:37:50.610 --> 00:37:52.610
I bet all these ingredients will
magically turn into a dessert.


611
00:37:52.850 --> 00:37:54.490
What!
No.


612
00:37:55.410 --> 00:37:57.650
Then go make it!
- Okay..


613
00:38:05.970 --> 00:38:08.450
Nobin!
Did you make any dessert..


614
00:38:09.490 --> 00:38:10.890
Oh, God!

615
00:38:11.250 --> 00:38:14.290
You haven't made anything yet!
What are you thinking?


616
00:38:14.410 --> 00:38:16.610
It has to go in..
- What!


617
00:38:18.330 --> 00:38:20.850
This guy is crazy!

618
00:38:21.730 --> 00:38:23.410
What the..
Goodness..


619
00:38:24.330 --> 00:38:27.730
Ice apples always drench me
in their juices!


620
00:38:34.250 --> 00:38:37.090
Hey! What happened?
- I got it.. - What..


621
00:38:37.170 --> 00:38:39.410
I got it..
- What? - I got it!


622
00:38:39.450 --> 00:38:42.570
Listen, get me about 50 mangoes.
- What! Mangoes?


623
00:38:42.650 --> 00:38:43.930
As many as you can get..
From anywhere you like..


624
00:38:44.090 --> 00:38:45.650
Raw mangoes, ripe mangoes..
From the trees.. On the ground..


625
00:38:45.770 --> 00:38:47.210
Get me everything you can find.
- Why? - Listen..


626
00:38:50.810 --> 00:38:51.890
Chandu..

627
00:38:53.770 --> 00:38:56.930
Do you see what I can see?
- Yes..


628
00:38:59.050 --> 00:39:02.810
I can see a fruit,
not a piece of sweet.


629
00:39:05.370 --> 00:39:07.370
Same here.
- 'Aam Sandesh.'


630
00:39:12.330 --> 00:39:13.650
The dessert worth mentioning
is the one I had


631
00:39:14.050 --> 00:39:15.570
at Mr. Maxwell's house.

632
00:39:18.050 --> 00:39:19.370
It's evident

633
00:39:19.930 --> 00:39:23.890
that this dessert was made
in an unhealthy manner.


634
00:39:25.130 --> 00:39:26.530
It's not fit to be consumed.

635
00:39:27.650 --> 00:39:29.610
I have written something
on this topic.


636
00:39:29.650 --> 00:39:31.930
It was published in Uncle Amrit's..
- Oh, stop it.


637
00:39:32.050 --> 00:39:34.450
Why mention academics
when we're having our meal?


638
00:39:35.530 --> 00:39:38.290
Listen, boy,
let me make something very clear..


639
00:39:38.650 --> 00:39:41.050
If this dessert.. - Mom..
- ...turns out to be terrible


640
00:39:41.850 --> 00:39:43.530
I'll suspend you from a rope

641
00:39:43.690 --> 00:39:45.290
with a fire burning beneath you.
Got it?


642
00:39:45.530 --> 00:39:47.770
No..
Why don't you all have one?


643
00:39:48.450 --> 00:39:51.770
If you don't like it, I'll accept
any punishment you give me.


644
00:40:22.090 --> 00:40:23.170
Go on, have it.

645
00:40:24.090 --> 00:40:25.170
Go on, eat.

646
00:40:29.010 --> 00:40:30.690
Hey..
What the..


647
00:40:37.810 --> 00:40:39.130
You've got talent, boy.

648
00:40:41.690 --> 00:40:42.610
Yes.

649
00:40:47.290 --> 00:40:50.130
How old are you?
What's your name?


650
00:40:50.810 --> 00:40:52.890
I'm 20 years old.
I'm Nobin.


651
00:40:53.050 --> 00:40:54.610
Nobin!
- Yes.


652
00:40:54.850 --> 00:40:56.490
You're a talented young thing.

653
00:40:57.010 --> 00:40:59.890
You've just started
getting a moustache.


654
00:41:00.410 --> 00:41:04.130
He's so very talented at such
a young age! - Yes.. - Nice..


655
00:41:04.530 --> 00:41:08.010
He's a magician..
- You've made my mouth water!


656
00:41:10.090 --> 00:41:12.410
Do you want to know what I think?

657
00:41:12.490 --> 00:41:14.650
It's like Malkanjaan's gatherings.

658
00:41:14.730 --> 00:41:18.010
No..
I won't let you go.


659
00:41:19.610 --> 00:41:20.890
Come..

660
00:41:22.050 --> 00:41:25.130
Hey, dearest.. Taste this..
- I wish to give you my regards.


661
00:41:25.450 --> 00:41:26.410
Come..

662
00:41:27.530 --> 00:41:30.050
Hey.. Sir..
Oh, God..


663
00:41:31.090 --> 00:41:33.090
Let him go..
- Oh, God.. My mom will scold me.


664
00:41:33.170 --> 00:41:34.330
Goodness..
Sir..


665
00:41:34.570 --> 00:41:37.250
1 anna..
This dessert costs 1 anna!


666
00:41:37.970 --> 00:41:39.450
Do you want my shop
to get closed down?


667
00:41:40.530 --> 00:41:43.410
Do you do all this intentionally
or are you plain stupid?


668
00:41:44.130 --> 00:41:47.090
Looks like you're getting used
to getting an applause. - No..


669
00:41:48.690 --> 00:41:50.290
The lady said..
- She said it


670
00:41:50.370 --> 00:41:52.090
and you ran at full speed
to make such a lavish sweet!


671
00:41:52.850 --> 00:41:54.850
Couldn't you tell her that this
sweet costs more than 1 anna?


672
00:41:55.410 --> 00:41:58.210
I
-I didn't calculate..

673
00:41:58.250 --> 00:42:01.410
You're usually a motormouth.
You argue with your elders.


674
00:42:01.610 --> 00:42:03.650
Go on!
Give him an answer!


675
00:42:04.170 --> 00:42:05.890
What happened?
Cat got your tongue?


676
00:42:06.250 --> 00:42:07.490
How are you going
to return the money?


677
00:42:07.730 --> 00:42:09.170
We won't give you a single penny!

678
00:42:10.210 --> 00:42:11.730
I ask for your forgiveness
on his behalf.


679
00:42:12.690 --> 00:42:14.170
He misunderstood it.

680
00:42:14.890 --> 00:42:16.490
Please forgive him this time.

681
00:42:16.850 --> 00:42:18.250
Please spare me, ma'am.

682
00:42:19.570 --> 00:42:21.410
I hired him
because Reba asked me to.


683
00:42:21.490 --> 00:42:22.610
I can't tolerate him any longer!

684
00:42:23.610 --> 00:42:25.050
You expect me to lose my shop,
which has been running for years


685
00:42:25.170 --> 00:42:26.090
just because
he wants to make something new?


686
00:42:26.130 --> 00:42:28.570
Well, I hope you now understand
who you've hired.


687
00:42:29.130 --> 00:42:30.530
He's blighted, cursed!

688
00:42:30.930 --> 00:42:32.530
He killed his father
even before he was born


689
00:42:33.050 --> 00:42:34.330
and now, he's after your life!

690
00:42:36.610 --> 00:42:39.330
You dare glare at us..
You dare glare at us!


691
00:42:40.050 --> 00:42:42.290
Can you do it? Will you be able
to return his money?


692
00:42:42.650 --> 00:42:43.690
Are you capable of doing that?

693
00:42:44.490 --> 00:42:45.970
What the..
- What the..


694
00:42:50.010 --> 00:42:50.890
Mom..

695
00:43:04.650 --> 00:43:05.530
Mom..

696
00:43:08.970 --> 00:43:09.850
Give these to him.

697
00:43:11.530 --> 00:43:12.410
Go on, take them.

698
00:43:16.130 --> 00:43:17.890
You all have done me many favours.

699
00:43:18.050 --> 00:43:19.690
Now, I don't need any help
from anyone.


700
00:43:21.850 --> 00:43:22.730
Thank you.

701
00:43:25.010 --> 00:43:25.970
Bless you.

702
00:43:32.810 --> 00:43:34.210
You think you're so intelligent!

703
00:43:34.890 --> 00:43:36.090
So, you don't want any help, right?

704
00:43:37.210 --> 00:43:39.130
You need to leave this house
in seven days!


705
00:43:39.650 --> 00:43:42.570
Seven days!
- Fine.


706
00:43:51.650 --> 00:43:52.770
No, that's not possible.

707
00:43:52.930 --> 00:43:54.650
All the people who work here
are old-school.


708
00:43:54.810 --> 00:43:55.890
All the sweets are old-fashioned.

709
00:43:55.970 --> 00:43:58.770
So, a new-age man like you
won't be able to do the work here.


710
00:43:58.890 --> 00:44:00.810
Come and get some curd..

711
00:44:01.130 --> 00:44:03.370
Fresh curd..

712
00:44:20.170 --> 00:44:22.530
Oh, the poor soul..
You're in misery..


713
00:44:23.130 --> 00:44:25.490
You're having to do this work
at this age.


714
00:44:26.290 --> 00:44:29.130
What else can you possibly do
when you have a crazy son?


715
00:44:29.810 --> 00:44:31.770
If you need money badly,
send him to our house.


716
00:44:32.170 --> 00:44:35.010
The garden needs to be tended to.
We'll give him some money.


717
00:44:35.210 --> 00:44:37.090
The Lord has given you
a healthy son.


718
00:44:37.410 --> 00:44:39.530
You need to put him to good use.
- I've heard


719
00:44:39.770 --> 00:44:41.850
that Nobin is cleaning
the toilets of people now.


720
00:44:41.930 --> 00:44:43.890
Good Lord!
It smells so bad!


721
00:44:46.170 --> 00:44:47.410
Let's go.
- Let's go.


722
00:44:50.010 --> 00:44:52.490
Did he use those dirty hands
to make sweets?


723
00:44:53.650 --> 00:44:55.330
Who knows..
