01:33:29.370 --> 01:33:30.490
I've seen Englishmen eat it.

1472
01:33:32.490 --> 01:33:33.370
Tell me what's in it.

1473
01:33:33.410 --> 01:33:34.490
I know what it is.

1474
01:33:35.090 --> 01:33:36.050
It's 'chhana'!

1475
01:33:36.130 --> 01:33:38.810
Yes, it is.
We call it cottage cheese.


1476
01:33:43.730 --> 01:33:46.370
Oh!
But how come it's so fine?


1477
01:33:46.490 --> 01:33:48.130
Your cottage cheese is rough.

1478
01:33:48.330 --> 01:33:50.890
We make it smoother.

1479
01:33:51.410 --> 01:33:52.490
You make it coarse
while the Englishmen


1480
01:33:52.530 --> 01:33:53.730
make it smoother.

1481
01:33:53.890 --> 01:33:54.770
Oh.

1482
01:33:56.810 --> 01:33:58.090
I have a request, sir.

1483
01:33:58.290 --> 01:33:59.130
Tell me.

1484
01:33:59.170 --> 01:34:03.690
C
-Can I see your kitchen?

1485
01:34:03.730 --> 01:34:06.290
I mean, can you show me the process

1486
01:34:06.490 --> 01:34:08.570
you follow
for preparing cottage cheese?


1487
01:34:08.610 --> 01:34:10.130
Sure.
- You will?


1488
01:34:10.210 --> 01:34:13.210
Of course I will.
But..


1489
01:34:14.650 --> 01:34:16.090
You'll have to sing another song.

1490
01:34:25.410 --> 01:34:27.890
Wow.
- Look.


1491
01:34:27.930 --> 01:34:29.010
This is your kitchen?

1492
01:34:31.450 --> 01:34:34.450
That's lemon.
We too..


1493
01:34:35.650 --> 01:34:36.490
Be patient.

1494
01:34:48.970 --> 01:34:50.290
That's whey.

1495
01:34:55.570 --> 01:34:57.530
So, adding the whey to the milk

1496
01:34:59.170 --> 01:35:00.570
is what makes the cheese so smooth.

1497
01:35:00.650 --> 01:35:01.970
So, that's the secret.

1498
01:35:02.690 --> 01:35:07.210
Sir, now, I'm going to use
this technique


1499
01:35:07.770 --> 01:35:09.450
in my invention, Rasgulla.

1500
01:35:10.570 --> 01:35:12.890
Rasgulla?
- A dumpling soaked in syrup.


1501
01:35:13.930 --> 01:35:15.570
Rasgulla.
What's that?


1502
01:35:15.770 --> 01:35:16.650
Well, sir..

1503
01:35:22.770 --> 01:35:24.210
It's my life.

1504
01:35:27.170 --> 01:35:28.370
It's the love of my life.

1505
01:35:29.170 --> 01:35:31.250
Love..

1506
01:35:32.050 --> 01:35:33.250
Remember, my young friend..

1507
01:35:33.810 --> 01:35:36.370
Love is all about keeping promises.

1508
01:35:43.850 --> 01:35:47.730
Rasgulla..
It will happen.


1509
01:35:54.690 --> 01:35:55.570
Nobin.

1510
01:35:59.250 --> 01:36:00.490
Where have you been, my son?

1511
01:36:01.370 --> 01:36:02.970
Why do you do this?

1512
01:36:03.250 --> 01:36:04.530
We've been so worried.

1513
01:36:04.650 --> 01:36:07.450
I won't do it again, I promise.

1514
01:36:10.770 --> 01:36:11.650
Go in.

1515
01:36:13.850 --> 01:36:16.930
Khirod!
My invention is going to work.


1516
01:36:18.650 --> 01:36:22.090
I went all the way to Bandel.

1517
01:36:22.210 --> 01:36:24.130
I met Mr. Paulo there.

1518
01:36:24.170 --> 01:36:27.690
He kept calling it Rasgulla.

1519
01:36:28.210 --> 01:36:29.730
Nice name, isn't it?
Rasgulla..


1520
01:36:29.770 --> 01:36:30.850
Hey, where are you going?

1521
01:36:33.490 --> 01:36:34.770
You'll do whatever you like

1522
01:36:34.810 --> 01:36:35.730
under the pretext of your invention

1523
01:36:35.770 --> 01:36:36.890
and we'll have to tolerate it!

1524
01:36:36.930 --> 01:36:38.370
No more excuses.

1525
01:36:38.770 --> 01:36:40.570
I'm sure it will work this time.
The Rasgulla.


1526
01:36:40.650 --> 01:36:41.850
Sweets again!

1527
01:36:41.890 --> 01:36:43.370
Is that all you ever think about?
- Yes!


1528
01:36:53.890 --> 01:36:55.010
You're always in my heart.

1529
01:36:56.450 --> 01:36:58.930
I know you'll hurt me again.

1530
01:36:59.210 --> 01:37:00.490
I won't hurt you again, Khirod.

1531
01:37:00.930 --> 01:37:03.530
I promise.
I swear on you.


1532
01:37:04.490 --> 01:37:06.450
This time, the Rasgulla will work.

1533
01:37:44.730 --> 01:37:45.690
Mr. Mahesh!

1534
01:37:54.130 --> 01:37:58.930
It works!
Our sweet is ready!


1535
01:38:20.930 --> 01:38:25.410
Where are we going?
- Don't you remember?


1536
01:38:39.370 --> 01:38:40.250
Here you go.

1537
01:38:42.370 --> 01:38:43.890
The sweet
that looks like the full moon.


1538
01:38:45.090 --> 01:38:46.970
I feed you every day.

1539
01:38:48.610 --> 01:38:50.530
Why don't you feed me today?

1540
01:38:51.410 --> 01:38:52.290
Me?

1541
01:41:22.490 --> 01:41:23.330
You know

1542
01:41:23.410 --> 01:41:25.090
a bridge
is about to be constructed here.


1543
01:41:25.410 --> 01:41:26.650
The journey
to Howrah Railway Station


1544
01:41:26.730 --> 01:41:28.090
on the other side
will become much easier.


1545
01:41:29.130 --> 01:41:30.090
That's all right.

1546
01:41:30.610 --> 01:41:31.970
But the construction
hasn't started yet.


1547
01:41:32.450 --> 01:41:35.410
They're just doing the publicity.

1548
01:41:35.530 --> 01:41:36.490
Publicity is important.

1549
01:41:37.010 --> 01:41:38.650
Just making something good
isn't enough.


1550
01:41:38.770 --> 01:41:41.490
People must be made to know
about it.


1551
01:41:41.610 --> 01:41:43.050
This new sweet you invented..

1552
01:41:43.250 --> 01:41:45.770
We must spread the word
about it too.


1553
01:41:46.210 --> 01:41:47.730
From now on, any customer who comes

1554
01:41:47.770 --> 01:41:49.490
to your shop,
should be served the Rasgulla


1555
01:41:49.650 --> 01:41:51.010
even if he doesn't buy anything.

1556
01:41:51.210 --> 01:41:52.090
Just like that.

1557
01:41:52.170 --> 01:41:54.130
You'll see,
it will build a market for you.


1558
01:41:54.290 --> 01:41:55.210
You know me so well.

1559
01:41:55.650 --> 01:41:58.130
I love serving people food.

1560
01:41:59.090 --> 01:42:01.210
But the financial aspect
is something


1561
01:42:01.250 --> 01:42:03.490
I don't like dealing with.

1562
01:42:06.250 --> 01:42:08.370
When will you grow up?

1563
01:42:10.130 --> 01:42:11.170
What's the use of growing up?

1564
01:42:12.250 --> 01:42:13.810
You're there for me.
- Yes.


1565
01:42:15.890 --> 01:42:17.930
Stop it!
People are looking.


1566
01:42:20.810 --> 01:42:21.690
Here you go.

1567
01:42:23.730 --> 01:42:26.730
Hello, Hemen.
Is Mr. Kalidas in? - Yes.


1568
01:42:28.250 --> 01:42:30.130
Hemen! - Yes?
- Go inside.


1569
01:42:30.250 --> 01:42:31.730
They can't find anything in there.

1570
01:42:32.450 --> 01:42:33.970
Why must I deal
with such nincompoops?


1571
01:42:35.610 --> 01:42:36.570
Yes?

1572
01:42:37.450 --> 01:42:38.850
Good morning, Mr. Kalidas.

1573
01:42:38.930 --> 01:42:40.730
Here are some Rasgullas from Nobin.

1574
01:42:40.930 --> 01:42:42.850
It's a novelty.
It's very nice.


1575
01:42:50.410 --> 01:42:52.810
Looks like the shop
isn't doing too well.


1576
01:42:53.730 --> 01:42:55.650
I see you're going door-to-door.

1577
01:42:56.570 --> 01:42:58.130
No, we're making decent sales.

1578
01:42:59.530 --> 01:43:02.010
Khirod said I should
distribute samples


1579
01:43:02.090 --> 01:43:03.850
of our novelty item to everyone.

1580
01:43:04.010 --> 01:43:06.210
What's so special
about these Rasgullas?


1581
01:43:06.250 --> 01:43:07.650
It's just another sweet.

1582
01:43:11.810 --> 01:43:15.770
The scent of love

1583
01:43:17.330 --> 01:43:18.970
long sleepless nights

1584
01:43:20.650 --> 01:43:22.450
and peace of mind
have gone into making it.


1585
01:43:23.810 --> 01:43:25.370
And most importantly

1586
01:43:26.690 --> 01:43:29.090
this is the answer
to all our struggles.


1587
01:43:30.450 --> 01:43:31.330
Leave.

1588
01:43:44.090 --> 01:43:45.290
Even flies won't sit on it.

1589
01:43:45.410 --> 01:43:48.730
Dad, I'm so thirsty!

1590
01:43:50.450 --> 01:43:52.690
You always need
something or the other.


1591
01:43:53.210 --> 01:43:55.730
You're either hungry or thirsty.

1592
01:43:56.970 --> 01:43:58.410
Wait, let me look.

1593
01:43:59.290 --> 01:44:01.170
Give me the sweets first.
Eight pieces of 'Gaja'.


1594
01:44:01.290 --> 01:44:04.290
I've eaten two and taken eight.
Ten in total.


1595
01:44:04.410 --> 01:44:06.610
Give it to me.
- How much for this?


1596
01:44:06.690 --> 01:44:08.010
Coachman!
- Yes, sir?


1597
01:44:08.090 --> 01:44:10.330
Stop the carriage at a place
where we can drink water.


1598
01:44:10.530 --> 01:44:11.410
Okay.

1599
01:44:11.490 --> 01:44:13.490
There are confectioneries
on either side of the road.


1600
01:44:13.650 --> 01:44:15.730
It's crowded outside
the shop on the left.


1601
01:44:16.050 --> 01:44:18.370
Okay.
- This one is closer.


1602
01:44:18.770 --> 01:44:19.850
Okay, dear.
Get down.


1603
01:44:23.650 --> 01:44:24.650
Come, my child.

1604
01:44:29.610 --> 01:44:30.650
Hello, sir.

1605
01:44:31.210 --> 01:44:32.570
Can I have some water to drink?

1606
01:44:32.810 --> 01:44:34.090
Yes.

1607
01:44:38.530 --> 01:44:40.130
No..
I don't need any sweets.


1608
01:44:40.210 --> 01:44:41.130
I just need some water.

1609
01:44:41.210 --> 01:44:42.090
Please have a seat.

1610
01:44:43.530 --> 01:44:45.050
Come.
- Please sit down.


1611
01:44:45.530 --> 01:44:46.570
We're Bengalis.

1612
01:44:47.930 --> 01:44:50.050
We don't serve people just water.

1613
01:44:50.650 --> 01:44:52.290
Please have some sweets
and then drink water.


1614
01:44:52.810 --> 01:44:53.810
Please have a seat.

1615
01:44:54.170 --> 01:44:55.530
Here you go.
Have it.


1616
01:44:55.970 --> 01:44:56.970
Hold it.

1617
01:44:59.490 --> 01:45:02.210
Dad, the sweet is delicious!

1618
01:45:02.250 --> 01:45:03.570
Is that so?

1619
01:45:06.690 --> 01:45:08.690
Is it nice, sir?
- What's this called?


1620
01:45:08.810 --> 01:45:10.290
It's called Rasgulla.

1621
01:45:10.330 --> 01:45:12.290
I'll take all of it.

1622
01:45:12.490 --> 01:45:15.450
You'll take all the Rasgullas?
- Yes, I will.


1623
01:45:16.370 --> 01:45:17.690
Parcel them.

1624
01:45:18.170 --> 01:45:19.410
Mahesh!

1625
01:45:19.490 --> 01:45:22.490
The sweet is delicious!
- Yes.


1626
01:45:22.610 --> 01:45:23.490
It's very nice.

1627
01:45:25.930 --> 01:45:26.850
Give me the sweets in a clay pot.

1628
01:45:28.770 --> 01:45:31.530
I'll take them
in a basket made of leaves.


1629
01:45:31.650 --> 01:45:32.730
I'll take extra syrup.

1630
01:45:32.850 --> 01:45:34.290
Please hurry up, mister!

1631
01:45:45.250 --> 01:45:46.210
Very nice!

1632
01:45:50.850 --> 01:45:51.930
Nobin's shop?

1633
01:45:58.890 --> 01:46:01.730
Where's my parcel?

1634
01:46:02.050 --> 01:46:03.490
Count how many people there are.

1635
01:46:03.650 --> 01:46:04.570
Sorry?

1636
01:46:08.850 --> 01:46:13.690
I want more.

1637
01:46:13.810 --> 01:46:15.330
Give me some.

1638
01:46:15.610 --> 01:46:16.490
Here it is.

1639
01:46:16.650 --> 01:46:17.690
And what about me?

1640
01:46:17.770 --> 01:46:19.930
There's this for you.

1641
01:46:20.210 --> 01:46:22.370
Rasgullas.
- Rasgullas!


1642
01:46:22.770 --> 01:46:25.170
Listen, give it to her quickly.
- Okay.


1643
01:46:27.410 --> 01:46:29.450
The gentleman sent this for you.

1644
01:46:42.010 --> 01:46:44.050
Mr. Sudhir, what's all this?

1645
01:46:44.130 --> 01:46:45.410
My son-in-law is visiting.

1646
01:46:45.650 --> 01:46:48.250
A whole Rohu fish
and a pot of Nobin's Rasgullas..


1647
01:46:48.370 --> 01:46:50.330
It's the least
I'll have to treat him to.


1648
01:46:50.410 --> 01:46:51.330
You're right.

1649
01:46:53.850 --> 01:46:55.010
I decide the price of milk.

1650
01:46:56.650 --> 01:46:58.450
Take it or leave it.

1651
01:47:12.690 --> 01:47:14.050
You seem to have lost your way.

1652
01:47:15.650 --> 01:47:18.410
I never thought you'd cross over
to my shop.


1653
01:47:20.410 --> 01:47:21.690
Lord Krishna had to cross the sea

1654
01:47:21.770 --> 01:47:22.970
when the situation demanded.

1655
01:47:25.330 --> 01:47:26.330
What do you need?

1656
01:47:27.250 --> 01:47:29.650
This monopoly
related to the price of milk


1657
01:47:30.370 --> 01:47:31.970
has to be stopped, isn't it?

1658
01:47:35.650 --> 01:47:37.530
Monopoly?
- You don't think so?


1659
01:47:38.330 --> 01:47:41.090
Previously, only Kashi charged
a premium amount.


1660
01:47:41.890 --> 01:47:43.850
Ever since my sales went up

1661
01:47:43.930 --> 01:47:45.890
all the milkmen have started
hiking their prices.


1662
01:47:45.970 --> 01:47:48.170
Your sales, your profit,
your problem.


1663
01:47:50.570 --> 01:47:52.210
You're an inventor.

1664
01:47:54.290 --> 01:47:55.290
Find a solution.

1665
01:47:55.850 --> 01:47:57.010
I'll find something all right

1666
01:47:57.970 --> 01:48:00.690
be it a sweet
or the solution to a problem.


1667
01:48:03.730 --> 01:48:05.050
Will the milkmen agree to it?

1668
01:48:06.890 --> 01:48:08.370
I alone can't stand up to them.

1669
01:48:08.730 --> 01:48:10.730
Unless we unite against them

1670
01:48:10.850 --> 01:48:12.730
they'll continue to harass us
like this.


1671
01:48:12.930 --> 01:48:14.970
Kalidas didn't agree to it.

1672
01:48:15.090 --> 01:48:16.290
Will the others cooperate?

1673
01:48:16.650 --> 01:48:18.010
Mr. Kalidas is scared of me.

1674
01:48:18.490 --> 01:48:20.090
But he respects you.
- I see.


1675
01:48:20.170 --> 01:48:21.890
If you agree to lend your support

1676
01:48:21.970 --> 01:48:23.530
I'll convince the others
to join us.


1677
01:48:23.650 --> 01:48:24.570
Goodness!

1678
01:48:25.170 --> 01:48:28.410
Nobin, both your behaviour
and your demeanour


1679
01:48:28.730 --> 01:48:30.050
have become sweet.

1680
01:48:30.490 --> 01:48:32.490
You all have got us
in a tight spot.


1681
01:48:33.530 --> 01:48:35.890
So, we've been compelled
to gather here.


1682
01:48:36.610 --> 01:48:38.450
Milkmen, please get this
loud and clear.


1683
01:48:39.370 --> 01:48:40.770
If you don't decide
on a uniform price


1684
01:48:40.850 --> 01:48:42.130
for the milk being sold
all over Kolkata


1685
01:48:42.650 --> 01:48:44.730
no confectioner will buy
a single drop of milk


1686
01:48:44.850 --> 01:48:46.050
from any of you.

1687
01:48:48.130 --> 01:48:51.810
So, tonight,
at the Bowbazar Milk Market


1688
01:48:52.010 --> 01:48:53.690
we'll decide
a standard price for milk


1689
01:48:54.010 --> 01:48:56.770
and all over Kolkata,
milk will be sold


1690
01:48:56.850 --> 01:48:58.210
at that very price.

1691
01:48:59.210 --> 01:49:01.650
How can you hike milk prices
as and when you please?


1692
01:49:02.130 --> 01:49:03.370
Do you have no shame?

1693
01:49:04.010 --> 01:49:05.490
Just because only the confectioners
are here


1694
01:49:05.610 --> 01:49:08.690
it doesn't mean that we
are the only consumers of milk.


1695
01:49:09.730 --> 01:49:12.250
Young children,
those who are unwell..


1696
01:49:12.810 --> 01:49:13.850
Even they consume milk.

1697
01:49:15.010 --> 01:49:18.770
Business doesn't mean
cheating people.


1698
01:49:21.330 --> 01:49:23.730
You can do business
in an ethical manner.


1699
01:49:24.770 --> 01:49:27.370
Those of you who agree to it
need to raise your hands.


1700
01:49:30.090 --> 01:49:31.050
Raise your hands.

1701
01:49:32.490 --> 01:49:33.810
Anyone?
Raise your hands, please!


1702
01:49:37.210 --> 01:49:39.370
What's your name?
- Ganguram!


